title: ‘Way too high’: Liberal Party's migration reduction plan is ‘still extremely high’
description: Microbusiness Chief Economist Leith Van Onselen criticises the Liberals' migration reduction plan.  “Let’s be honest, 200,000 net overseas migration is still extremely high,” Mr Van Onselen told Sky News host Andrew Bolt.  “The Liberals basically just want to take us back to pre-pandemic levels of immigration, which, as I said, is still way too high.  “We should also focus that on genuine skills that the country actually needs rather than more Uber drivers.”

title: Australians ‘pay the price’ for Albanese government’s failure
description: Shadow Home Affairs Minister Jonathon Duniam says Australians “pay the price” for the Albanese government’s failure.  Mr Duniam told Sky News host Peta Credlin that the government fails on “basic inputs of data”.  “How many houses, how many hospital beds, how many school places are going to be available?”

title: UN Security Council approves Trump’s plan for Gaza stabilisation
description: Deputy Foreign Minister Sharren Haskel is concerned there has not been enough pressure on Hamas despite the UN Security Council endorsement of the US plan to establish an international stabilisation force in Gaza.  “It really depends on the international community and how much pressure they are willing to put on Hamas,” Ms Haskel told Sky News host Chris Kenny.  “Hamas is defying even the first stage of the ceasefire, constantly shooting, sending drones, and the most important thing, hasn’t returned all the hostages yet.  “If there’s not going to be massive international pressure now … we are going to face two choices, whether they are going to continue putting that pressure through going diplomatic means or who's going to disarm them.”

title: ‘There needs to be an inquiry’: Albanese pressed on Brittany Higgins questions
description: GXO Strategies Director Cameron Milner comments on Prime Minister Anthony Albanese’s handling of questions related to Brittany Higgins.   “It’s a protection racket for his thugs in the Senate," Mr Milner told Sky News host Andrew Bolt.  “This is the disgusting heart of this thing.  “There needs to be an inquiry.”

title: ‘Great sin’: ABC operates like a ‘gang of thieves’
description: Sky News host Andrew Bolt discusses the “great sin” of the ABC.  Mr Bolt said the ABC is denying its “bias” to left wing political views.  “I'll be blunt, the ABC actually operates like a gang of thieves.”

title: ‘It should be overturned’: Daughter of IRGC general living in Australia
description: Shadow Assistant Treasurer Dave Sharma analyses the concern over an IRGC general’s daughter being granted access to Australia.   “It deserves close examination, and I think it should be overturned,” Mr Sharma told Sky News host Sharri Markson.  “This general … has been on Australia’s autonomous sanctions list for a number of years."

title: Immigrants coming to Australia must ‘respect’ the values
description: Shadow Home Affairs Minister Jonathon Duniam says the immigrants coming to Australia need to “share our values”.  Mr Duniam said it’s important they also “uphold the rule of law”.  “Respect our democracy and the freedoms that come with it.”

title: ​ The Epstein controversy is ‘tearing apart’ the MAGA movement
description: Sky News host Sharri Markson states US President Donald Trump’s attempt to end the war in Russia and Ukraine has been “repeatedly derailed” by the Epstein files.  “This controversy has begun to overshadow much of his agenda,” Ms Markson said.  “It is also tearing apart the Republican Party, particularly the MAGA movement.”

title: Two-state Gaza plan is the 'easiest condition' to meet
description: Former Israeli politician Einat Wilf believes Saudi Arabia's desire for a two-state Gaza plan is the “easiest condition” to meet.  “The pathway to one more Arab state … is the same one it has been for the past century,” Ms Wilf told Sky News host Sharri Markson.  “That the Arabs of the West Bank and Gaza, the Palestinians, will finally decide that it’s more important for them to build a state for themselves, rather than destroy the Jewish state.”

title: Energy policy is a complete ‘trainwreck’: Sussan Ley
description: Opposition Leader Sussan Ley discusses "affordable energy policy” and “responsible” emissions reduction.  “Energy policy is a complete trainwreck and we have to restore some sort of discipline,” Ms Ley told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “When energy is unaffordable, everything is unaffordable.”

title: ‘Mind-numbingly dumb’: US passes bill to release Epstein files
description: Townhall.com senior columnist Kurt Schlichter describes the entire Epstein file debacle as one of the most “mind-numbingly dumb” things in American politics.  This comes as Congress has passed a bill to release the Epstein files.  “It’s one of the most mind-numbingly dumb things in American politics,” Mr Schlichter told Sky News host Sharri Markson.   “Jeffrey Epstein was an American pervert who killed himself in jail waiting to go to prison for the rest of his life.”

title: ‘Disappointment’: Ley calls out Albanese for surge in power bills
description: Opposition Leader Sussan Ley says power bills are surging under Labor as the government is taking a “backward step”.  “Reliability is going down, prices are going up, emissions are flatlining … the job is not being done,” Ms Ley told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “As I travel around, I am hearing a real sense of disappointment in this prime minister.  “Explain to Australians what’s going on.”

title: Power bills increase as more Australians encounter financial hardship
description: Sky News host Paul Murray states that Australians are currently struggling to pay their bills, as evidenced by the rise in electricity costs, a component of the ongoing cost-of-living crisis.  “Australians are having a struggle right now when it comes to paying the bills,” Mr Murray said.  “This represents itself constantly as the refrain of cost-of-living, cost-of-living, cost-of-living.  “Clearly, one of the things that keeps going up is power bills.”

title: ‘Strange’: Manchester bar bans solo drinkers during late hours
description: Sky News host Freya Leach explains why a bar in Greater Manchester doesn't permit people to enter alone.   “A bar in Greater Manchester has some very strange entry requirements, one of them is that they will not accept people entering the bar by themselves,” Ms Leach said.  “You have to be in a group, they will not let you come in if you are a singular individual.”

title: ‘Party-pooper’: Busking hotspots created after Clover Moore ban
description: ​Sky News host Caleb Bond calls Lord Mayor Clover Moore a “party-pooper” for heavily restricting busking.  “The Minns government in New South Wales has turned around and said Clover Moore, up yours, how dare you do this?” Mr Bond said.  “They have now designated 16 new sites in the CBD where you can go and busk.”
